===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|blessen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term/t|ang|blētsian}}, {{term/t|ang|blēdsian||to consecrate ''(with blood)''}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*blōþisōną||to sprinkle, mark or hallow with blood}}, from {{term/t|gem-pro|*blōþą||blood}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*bhlo-to-||to gush, spurt}}, from {{term/t|ine-pro|*bhol-}}, {{term/t|ine-pro|*bhlē-dh-}}, {{term/t|ine-pro|*bhlō(w)-||to thrive, flourish, bloom}}. Cognate with {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|bletza||to bless|lang=non}} (whence {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|blessa|lang=is}}), {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term/t|ang|blēdan||to bleed}}. More at {{term|bleed|lang=en}}.

